*** Map is now open source (under a Creative Commons license) - 2010.02.05 ***
I don't have time to work on this map so I release it again under a open source license.

The package now contains source and compiled versions of all earlier versions of this map.

*** Suspended - 2007.12.12 ***
This map wasn't any success because of it's huge size and layout (players got lost!). I've learned from my faults and I'm now making a new zombie map from ground up. This time I will focus on gameplay and performance, and as much as possible will be documented and carefully planned.
***

A large area with glass ways along the high mountain wall. Under the map there are two floors; the basement and the dark sub-basement. A control room in the basement has buttons to control various doors, including a monitor (connected to 16 cameras) to show the activity around the map. This map also have a large blue room with low gravity.

Features of this map:
* A cannon that shoots you high up in the air across the entire map.
* Trampolines. These must be used to get to certain locations, like some glass platforms.
* A control room with a 3D mini-map of the basement, buttons to control the doors around the map and a monitor connected to 16 cameras.
* A blue room with low gravity and large as the rest of the map.
* A lot of teleports (with symbols that shows where it takes you.
* Anti-camping stuff to avoid unfair camping (hurt and push triggers).

This map is very big and may not be that funny if there are only 10 players on it. Recommended amount of players is at least 30. If there are too few players it may be a bit difficult to find eachother.

Note: The screenshots are simple, and some of them are taken from a earlier version.

Made by: Richard Helgeby (with some ideas from Nikmann).
Testing by: Nikmann [NOR] and the players of the SwissQuake zombie server.

On 2312, after the disaster with the zombies on Earth, the humans decided to make their experiences with undead people in the space. They evacuated the Xblah Mothership to make government only experiences. But an undead escaped from his jail, and them started to infect everyone there.

Now the solution is with you!

Kill all the zombies, be infected, or blow up the Xblah Mothership.

INSTALL -  Place the BSP in ... This directory...
C:/ProgramFiles/Steam/SteamApps/Name/CounterStrikeSource/Cstrike/Maps Folder


#TeamZombie

zm_monastery by Soft Serve

A medieval monastery located in a hidden inlet.

For this map, I took a lot of inspiration from Dark Souls' vertical level design, in particular the Painted World of Ariamis and Sen's Fortress areas.

A defensive ZM map with very little barricading.

You start out running for the glass gates until someone becomes infected. Then you must destroy the glass panels to prevent the zombies from getting to you while trying to flee pass the last glass gate. The final 2 rooms have places you can dodge the zombies from.

A few secrets can help you dodge the zombies but there's also counter-secrets to hiding spots.

First thing's first...TURN OFF ZOMBIE FOG WHEN PLAYING THIS MAP! honestly it takes away from the mood of the map and makes it look a lot uglier.

All the info's in the read me document packaged with the rar.

GOOD NEWS! THE MAP IS FINALLY OPTIMIZED! I figured out how to fix my map thanks to more research...

This map supports up to 56 players. I recommend playing this version on smaller servers since it's only a 1 story elementary school at the moment. Now that this is optimized I can concentrate on making a zm_midwich_2f!

Remember...lots of secrets/hidden doors. There's only ONE room that I know of where there isn't a 2nd way to get inside. Scratch and claw your way around walls, floors, etc. to see if you can break into rooms to attack humans.

Enjoy the map. ;) Thanks for all the wonderful comments on my first iteration of the map!

P.S. I've added one more camp spot for the humans. You should be able to notice if you've played my first version of the map.
